1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:03,800
Sometimes we'll need to know whether an item is in a list or not.

2

00:00:03,800  -->  00:00:09,760
You can use in and not in to check if an item exists in that list.

3

00:00:09,760  -->  00:00:16,260
This is like asking, is apple in my cart or is Sam in the list of students?

4

00:00:16,260  -->  00:00:20,600
These operators allow us the ability to search within

5

00:00:20,600  -->  00:00:25,500
the data collection and let us know if our item of interest is there or not.

6

00:00:25,500  -->  00:00:29,095
Sometimes you just need to do a quick check.

7

00:00:29,095  -->  00:00:32,990
Let's check out an example where in and not in

8

00:00:32,990  -->  00:00:37,870
operators can come in handy for searching through a list to find an item.

9

00:00:37,870  -->  00:00:41,890
For example, let's create an array of fruits again,

10

00:00:41,890  -->  00:00:45,670
where we'll say fruit is our variable name,

11

00:00:45,670  -->  00:00:48,290
and we'll set that equal to a list of apple,

12

00:00:48,290  -->  00:00:51,310
banana, and cherry, which are three different strings.

13

00:00:51,310  -->  00:00:55,130
If we want to check if apple is in our list of fruits,

14

00:00:55,130  -->  00:00:58,650
we could do this fairly easily if there were only three items in the list,

15

00:00:58,650  -->  00:01:00,885
because we can just see that it's there.

16

00:01:00,885  -->  00:01:04,260
And we can also simply count through the items as well.

17

00:01:04,260  -->  00:01:08,680
But what if there were tens or hundreds of items or even thousands?

18

00:01:08,680  -->  00:01:12,360
This could take a huge amount of time to manually check through the list.

19

00:01:12,360  -->  00:01:15,460
This is where we can use our in operator to check

20

00:01:15,460  -->  00:01:18,620
if apple exists within the fruits array.

21

00:01:18,620  -->  00:01:21,775
We'll write an if statement and ask if apple

22

00:01:21,775  -->  00:01:25,740
exists in the fruits list and then print a message.

23

00:01:25,740  -->  00:01:28,295
We'll do this by writing an if statement,

24

00:01:28,295  -->  00:01:33,245
and we'll say if apple in fruits,

25

00:01:33,245  -->  00:01:36,300
then print a string,

26

00:01:36,300  -->  00:01:39,850
and we'll say apple is in the list with an exclamation point,

27

00:01:39,850  -->  00:01:41,070
then we'll close out the quotes,

28

00:01:41,070  -->  00:01:42,450
and then we'll close out the print statement.

29

00:01:42,450  -->  00:01:46,450
What do you think will happen if we run this code?

30

00:01:46,660  -->  00:01:52,245
Let's find out. We do see that it's print out apple is in the list.

31

00:01:52,245  -->  00:01:57,090
Since apple does exist in our fruits list above,

32

00:01:57,090  -->  00:02:00,745
when our code runs, we in fact see the success message printed out,

33

00:02:00,745  -->  00:02:02,940
apple is in the list.

34

00:02:02,960  -->  00:02:08,325
We can also check if something is not in the list with the not in operator.

35

00:02:08,325  -->  00:02:12,460
Let's check if grape is in the fruits array.

36

00:02:12,460  -->  00:02:17,740
We'll define another if statement and ask if grape is not in the fruits list.

37

00:02:17,740  -->  00:02:20,840
Since we've already declared the fruits list above,

38

00:02:20,840  -->  00:02:23,485
we can then write our if statement here.

39

00:02:23,485  -->  00:02:26,300
We can say, if grape,

40

00:02:26,300  -->  00:02:33,510
not in fruits, then print grape is not in the list.

41

00:02:33,510  -->  00:02:36,240
Then we'll close out that print statement.

42

00:02:36,240  -->  00:02:40,880
Can you guess what the output of this cell is going to be?

43

00:02:43,740  -->  00:02:47,300
By running this code, since grape is not in the list,

44

00:02:47,300  -->  00:02:50,060
we see the message of print,

45

00:02:50,060  -->  00:02:51,720
grape is not in the list,

46

00:02:51,720  -->  00:02:55,320
and that's because we only have three items in our fruit list,

47

00:02:55,320  -->  00:02:56,460
which is apple, banana,

48

00:02:56,460  -->  00:02:58,760
and cherry, so grape is not in that.

49

00:02:58,760  -->  00:03:02,820
Now we know a couple of very handy and versatile ways to search

50

00:03:02,820  -->  00:03:08,580
whether certain items are in our lists or not. Great work.
